Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.75,0:00:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,今天对我们的星球来说是一个暗淡的周年纪念日。\NToday marks a bleak anniversary for our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.50,0:00:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,自从三年前第一例植物病毒发现后\N{\i1}Three years ago the first case of a global plant virus was reported,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.68,0:00:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,一场瘟疫便开始席卷并摧毁了几乎全部的生态系统\N{\i1}which started to ravage most of our ecosystems.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.97,0:01:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,世界领先的研究实验室\N{\i1}The world's leading research laboratories{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,...曾经努力着试图阻止这个致命病毒的扩散\N{\i1}have been trying to find a way to stop this deadly pathogen,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.20,0:01:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但到目前为止，他们都没有成功。\N{\i1}but so far their efforts have been unsuccessful.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.77,0:01:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,最近的研究表明，食用受病毒污染食物的人...\N{\i1}The latest research shows that people who consume food infected with a virus{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.75,0:01:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,...自身也将产生严重的自身免疫性疾病。\N{\i1}develop severe autoimmune diseases.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.31,0:01:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,此外，大量减少的植物将会影响大气中的氧气含量。\N{\i1}In addition, the loss of plant life has contributed to the concentration{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.86,0:01:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,...大气中的氧气浓度达到 18%，\N{\i1}of oxygen in the atmosphere to decrease to 18%.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.49,0:01:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,创历史新低。\N{\i1}The lowest on record.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.36,0:01:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,迅速消失的森林无法维持氧循环的平衡\N{\i1}The rapidly disappearing forest cannot recycle{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.37,0:01:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...这样的低氧水平将会长期存在\N{\i1}enough carbon dioxide to maintain these level for much longer.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.96,0:01:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这些大气变化导致世界范围内自然灾害的增加。\N{\i1}These atmospheric changes have caused an increase in natural disasters around the globe.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.46,0:01:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,当氧气含量低于 10% 时，人们就会开始窒息。\N{\i1}As oxygen levels drop below 10%, people will begin to suffocate.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.42,0:01:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我们美丽的地区家园将要毁灭。\N{\i1}Our beautiful planet Earth is doomed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.05,0:01:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但人类仍有生存的机会。\N{\i1}But humanity still has a chance of survival.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.76,0:01:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我们最大的希望，由史蒂文罗斯博士开发的双子座计划。\N{\i1}And their best hope is Project Gemini developed by Dr. Steven Ross.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.18,0:01:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,该项目起源于8年前的一项考古发现一群古生物学家\N{\i1}The project centers around an archaeological find discovered eight years ago by a group of paleontologists{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.70,0:01:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,发现了两件奇特的物体与外星起源相关联\N{\i1}who found two unique objects of extraterrestrial origin.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.28,0:02:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,这些文物估计有超过 40 亿年的历史。\N{\i1}The artifacts were estimated to be more than four billion years old.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.49,0:02:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,斯蒂芬霍金曾经说过...\NStephen Hawking once said,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.37,0:02:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,...如果人类想要长久的生存下去...\Nthat if humans are to survive long term,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.20,0:02:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...就必须找到离开地球的方法。\Nwe must find a way to get off planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.83,0:02:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,他对我们的机遇相当乐观\NHe was optimistic about our chances,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.25,0:02:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,结果也证明他是对的\Nand in fact, as it turns out he was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.17,0:02:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,这些奇特物件比生命本身更早出现在地球上。\NThese unique devices that we found appeared on Earth before life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.43,0:02:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不知道是什么外星高等智慧创造了它们并将它们留在这里......\NWe don't know what mysterious Stellar wisdom created them and left them here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.64,0:02:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,...但我们在濒临灭亡时收到这些礼物。\Nbut we've received this gift on the brink of extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.69,0:02:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我们试图逆向研究这球体和引擎的材料\NWe managed to recreate this pseudo tough materials**
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.15,0:02:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,...然后成功地重建了它。\Nthat the Sphere and the Engine are made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.49,0:02:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我们完美地复制了这两件物件。\NAnd we precisely copied both of the devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.28,0:02:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们拥有两件完全一样的设备。\NNow each of them has an identical twin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.54,0:02:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,引擎用于星际飞行船舶的发动机。\NThe Warp Engine for interstellar flights
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.83,0:03:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,使我们能够找到一颗几乎适合地球化的行星。\Nhas allowed us to find a planet more or less suitable for terraforming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的无人卫星对系外行星TESS进行勘测\NThe unmanned vehicle completed a jump to the solar system TESS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.13,0:03:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,...那些传回来的资料和样本证实了我们的理论\Nand returned with information and samples that confirmed our theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.31,0:03:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,而这个球体,是用来创造生命的\NAnd this device, this Sphere is for creating life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.02,0:03:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,经过多年的研究，我们发现了一种控制这球体和引擎的方法。\NAfter years of research,we discovered a way to control the Sphere and the Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.19,0:03:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这些物体有他们自己的语言。\NThese devices have their own unique language.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.07,0:03:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经解码了几十条命令，\NWe decoded dozens of commands,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.32,0:03:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,每条命令对应一个特定的模式。\Neach of which corresponds to a certain pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.49,0:03:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这道初始命令对应的模式\NThis pattern gave the initial command,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.00,0:03:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,球体曾经连续执行了40亿年\Nand the Sphere began to carry out more than four billion years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.98,0:04:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,它利用环境中的化学元素开始创造真正的奇迹：\NThe Sphere uses chemical elements from the environment and creates a true miracle:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.69,0:04:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,生命\Nlife!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.53,0:04:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在知道地球上的生命是由这台机器创造的。\NNow we know life on Earth was created by this machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.95,0:04:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,这个球体是我们计划的起点。\NThe Sphere is our starting point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.49,0:04:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,让我向您介绍我们一群领先的研究科学家的团队\NLet me introduce you to our team of leading research scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.92,0:04:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我们团队的成员有：彼得雷曼 博士。\NOur team consists of: Dr. Peter Lehmann,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,外星飞船引擎专家。\Na specialist in extraterrestrial Warp Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.97,0:04:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,莱昂娜·雷德伍德 博士。\NDoctor Leona Redwood,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.72,0:04:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,地球化计划创始人。\Na terraforming program builder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.81,0:04:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,今天加入我们的是由瑞安康纳少校军事训练过的飞行员们。\NToday we are joined by military trained pilots,headed by Major Ryan Connor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.02,0:04:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们正在前往太阳系外行星的路上。\NWe are departing for the solar system TESS,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.40,0:04:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,距离这里几百光年的地方。\Nseveral hundred light years from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.32,0:04:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将在适当的条件下将球体带到行星上。\NWe will bring The Sphere to a planet that has the right conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.87,0:05:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,带来我们的地球 2.0。\NAnd we'll create Earth 2.0,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.54,0:05:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,人类的新家园。\Na new home for humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.54,0:05:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,双子座计划
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.12,0:08:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么看，彼得？\NWhat do you think, Peter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.91,0:08:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,创造这些的家伙现在在哪里？\NWhoever created this, where are they now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,没有足够的数据可以说明。\NThere's not enough data to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.71,0:08:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我不喜欢猜测这些事情。\NAnd I don't really like speculating about stuff like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.21,0:08:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是毫无根据的猜测。 这是有依据的理论。\NThis isn't about the speculation.It's a theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.97,0:08:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,也许来自一个失落的文明。\NMaybe it was a lost civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.05,0:08:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,在高度发达文明中自我毁灭掉了……\NWe know from experience how highly-developed civilizations are good at self-destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.14,0:08:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,谁知道呢?     是的。\N-Who knows?  -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.21,0:09:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,对人类来说，这算是一次飞跃了，对吧？\NWell, another giant leap for humanity, eh, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.51,0:09:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,历史上第一次巨大进步。\NOnly this time literally,for the first time in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.85,0:09:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,只要比一团原子多的东西, 就能成为我们未来的家园\NJust as long as something more than a bunch of atoms makes it to the destination…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.35,0:09:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,那也算是了。\NIt still counts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.73,0:09:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,说啊,历史上的第一次。\NSay it. For the first time in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.94,0:09:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,注意了，准备空间跳跃。\NAttention! And prepare for a jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.94,0:10:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,所有系统已就绪。\NAll systems are ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.03,0:10:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,坐标已设置。\NThe coordinates are set.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.44,0:10:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,空间引擎设置为最大功率\NWarp Drive set at maximum power.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.82,0:10:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,准备？\NReady?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.53,0:10:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,开始\NEngage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.95,0:11:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,致命错误。\N{\i1}Critical error.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.29,0:11:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,致命错误。\N{\i1}Critical error.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.71,0:11:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,致命错误。\N{\i1}Critical error.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.09,0:11:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,致命错误。\N{\i1}Critical error.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.46,0:12:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在哪？\NWhere are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.26,0:12:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这是TESS吗？\NIs this TESS?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.39,0:12:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,理查德，我们达到指定位置了吗？\NRichard, did we complete the maneuver?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.52,0:13:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，我们到了。\NYes, we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.77,0:13:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,星图...并不匹配。\NStar maps…They don't match up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.65,0:13:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是TESS。\NIt's not TESS.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.20,0:13:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,什么坐标，你投进去了吗？\NWhat coordinates.did you put in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.37,0:13:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定你输入了正确的坐标?\NAre you sure they were operational?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.79,0:13:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，长官。\NOf course, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.75,0:13:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你检查过引擎吗？\NDid you check the Engine?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.96,0:13:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都按照计划进行。\NEverything was done according to protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.55,0:13:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,如果一切都按照计划来...\NIf everything was done to protocol,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.17,0:13:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...我们现在就应该在 TESS。\Nwe'd be in TESS right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.84,0:13:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,任务失败了，彼得。\NThe mission failed, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.89,0:13:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,地球已经没有希望了。\NThere is no hope for Earth now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.02,0:13:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 请求许可检查引擎？               - 不。\N-Permission to check the Engine.   -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.27,0:13:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你渎职了。\NYou are relieved of your duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.52,0:13:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,回到在你的休息室直到我另有命令。\NStay in your bunk until I say otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.86,0:13:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,是, 长官。\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.76,0:14:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么？\NWhat's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.39,0:15:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,在物理......有一个方程称为狄拉克方程。\NIn physics,there is an equation… The Dirac equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.69,0:15:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,当两个粒子相互接触，\NWhen two particles come into contact,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.19,0:15:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,它们将永远彼此相连系。\Nthey become bound forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.82,0:15:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管将他们分隔数光年，他们仍然"感受"着彼此。\NThey continue to "feel" one another,even if they are light years apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.41,0:15:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这被称为量子纠缠。\NIt's called quantum entanglement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.91,0:15:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,所以这对你来说是物理学?\NThat's physics for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.88,0:15:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,这不仅仅是物理学。\NNot just physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.21,0:16:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,尝试调整跳跃轨迹。\NTry de-set the jump trajectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.71,0:16:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,也许这会让我们知道我们的位置。\NMaybe it will help us figure out where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.34,0:16:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,不，史蒂夫。轨迹不清晰。\NNo, Steve.The trajectory is not clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.97,0:16:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,数据没有任何意义。\NThe data doesn't make any sense at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.89,0:16:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我们好像进入了第四维度\NWe've entered the fourth dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.47,0:16:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但又好像是移动了坐标轴一样,我们无法到达目的地……\NBut it's almost as if we moved along the coordinates axis that we can't access.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.43,0:16:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我们又跳回了三维空间。\NAnd then we jumped back into three-dimensional space.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.86,0:16:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们现在在哪里？\NBut where?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.16,0:16:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的环境中有什么东西可以帮助我们找到自己的位置吗？\NIs there anything around us that can help us figure out our location?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.63,0:16:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,不, 没有参照物。也没有什么是已知的。\NNo, no land marks.Nothing even remotely familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.80,0:17:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我们没有任何数据可以跳回去。\NWe have no point to set a return jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.18,0:17:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,什么意思？\NSo that means
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.35,0:17:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,直到我们知道我们在哪里之前我们没法回去。\Nthat until we figure out where we are we can't get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.18,0:17:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,确实。\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.10,0:17:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"维修气闸打开"\N{\i1}Repair airlock is open.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.44,0:17:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么？\NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.83,0:17:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,发动机区域的维修气闸打开了。\NThe repair airlock of the Engine compartment is open.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.65,0:17:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,什么情况？ 有人在那吗？\NWhy? And who is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.83,0:17:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,气闸，回复,这里是船长。 气闸那有人的话请回答。\NRepair airlock, this is the captain calling. Airlock, report.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.41,0:17:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"不明物体接近"\N{\i1}Unidentified object approaching.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.63,0:17:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"不明物体接近"\N{\i1}Unidentified object approaching.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.80,0:17:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"不明物体接近"\N{\i1}Unidentified object approaching.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.81,0:17:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"不明物体接近"\N{\i1}Unidentified object approaching.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.31,0:17:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"不明物体接近"\N{\i1}Unidentified object approaching.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.75,0:18:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,妈的！\NShit!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.27,0:18:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,这些都是啥破事啊\NI can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.10,0:18:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,冷静点，蕾欧娜。\NCalm down, Leona.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.52,0:18:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,想活下来的话，我们必须保持冷静。\NWe gotta keep our cool if we wanna survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.86,0:18:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经失去了一名队友。\NWe are already a man down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.33,0:18:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得无视史蒂夫的命令，去了发动机区。\NPeter ignored Steve's orders,went to the Engine compartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.04,0:18:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,他认为他把我们带到了错误的地方，然后他结束了自己的生命。\Nrealised what he'd done,and that was the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.26,0:18:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得不会那样做！\NPeter wouldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.97,0:19:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我了解他！\NI knew him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.26,0:19:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我和他一起工作了8年！\NI worked with him for eight years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.89,0:19:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他不会那么轻易放弃的！\NHe couldn't given up so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.94,0:19:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,莱昂，够了！\NLeona, enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.61,0:19:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,不该是这样为他求情的！\NHow can you defend him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.73,0:19:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们必须处理他造成的错误后果。\NNow we have to deal with the results of his mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.03,0:19:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,做他本该做好的工作。\NDo his work for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.99,0:19:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,一个人把我们全体拖下水。\NOne person put multiple lives in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.62,0:19:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他几乎摧毁了人类唯一的生存机会！\NHe almost destroyed humanity's only chance of survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.91,0:19:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,这才应该是你流泪的理由\NThat's who you should be crying for?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.45,0:20:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,丽塔死后，我也不想活了。\NAfter Rita died I didn't wanna live anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.04,0:20:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我想了比起一了百了\NBut then I thought,instead of ending it all
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.08,0:20:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我还可以做一些有意义的事情。\NI could make it mean something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.21,0:20:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我决定全身心地投入到这项任务中。\NSo I decided to devote myself to the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,但事实证明...\NBut now it turns out
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.18,0:20:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,现在的我比在地球上更无能。\Nthat I'm less useful here than on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.86,0:20:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫。\NDavid…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.82,0:20:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都会好的,  我们总会有办法的。\NEverything will be all right.We'll find a way out this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.82,0:20:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的未来就靠我们的任务成败与否。\NThe future of Earth depends on our mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.66,0:20:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,放弃不是我们的选择。\NGiving up is not an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.75,0:20:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须确定我们在哪维宇宙。\NWe need to establish what part of the universe we're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.21,0:20:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,-理查德，你知道什么些吗？\N-Richard, do you have anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.25,0:20:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-还没有。\N-Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.96,0:21:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟踪最近的恒星和行星的运动轨迹。\NI'm tracking the moving trajectories of the nearest stars and planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.13,0:21:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,以此试着计算我们的位置。\NI'll try to calculate our position from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.64,0:21:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫。那颗星球怎么样？\NDavid, what about that planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.81,0:21:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,传感器有数据吗？\NAny data on the probe?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.64,0:21:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,刚刚接收。\NJust loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.44,0:21:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,好的。\NGreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.07,0:21:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,这颗行星的表面是由火山岩组成的。\NThe surface of the planet is made of volcanic rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.36,0:21:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,没有生命。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.37,0:21:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,有大气但没有氧气。\NThere is an atmosphere,but without oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.95,0:21:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,平均温度为16摄氏度。\NThe average temperature is 16 degrees Celsius.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.83,0:21:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,外部环境也对人也不算危险。\NThe outside environment isn't aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.75,0:21:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要的只是呼吸器。\NAll we'll need are breathing masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.38,0:21:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,那不错啊。\NIt's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.22,0:21:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我必须在TESS和这个星球之间做出选择……\NIf I could choose between TESS and this planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.97,0:21:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,...我也许会去这里。\NI'd go here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.65,0:22:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我们有多幸运吗？\NDo you realize how lucky we are?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.44,0:22:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,找到适合球体的行星的几率有多大？\NWhat was the likelihood of winding up near planet that's perfect for the Sphere?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.74,0:22:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,如果这不是意外呢？\NWhat if this isn't an accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.57,0:22:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说如果我们是被引导到这里的怎么办？\NWhat if we were brought here on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.00,0:22:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,谁会这么做？   "他们",和"他们"给我们留下了球体不是一回事吗?\N-By whom?       -The same thing that left us the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.21,0:22:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞恩，准备登陆星球。                你什么意思？\N-Ryan, get ready to disembark.   -What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.71,0:22:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以在这个星球上完成我们的使命。\NWe can complete our mission on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.42,0:22:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们还没有检查过它。\NBut we haven't examined it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.38,0:22:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,但这是我们仅有的机会。\NBut this is our chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.30,0:22:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们将球体发射到这个星球上...\NIf we launch the Sphere on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.01,0:22:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我们也有足够的时间去搞清楚我们在哪。\Nwe'll have enough time to understand where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.35,0:22:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,这样，其他舰船就可以跃迁到我们这来。\NThen, other ships come repeat our job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.64,0:22:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,理查德，准备着陆器降落在这个星球上。\NRichard, prepare the lander to go down to the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.23,0:22:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,但这是一颗年轻的星球。 大气不稳定。\NBut it's a young planet,the atmosphere is unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.94,0:22:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我们对这个星球一无所知。\NWe don't know anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.44,0:22:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,降落在地面上可能不安全。\NIt might not be safe to make a surface landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.03,0:22:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我同意。 你鲁莽地冒着船员安全风险。\NI agree, you're recklessly risking the safety of the crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.41,0:22:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我反对。\NAnd I'm against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.16,0:22:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,幸运的是，我是做出最终决定的人。\NThankfully, I am the one who makes the final decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.45,0:22:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,不，史蒂夫，现在做出这样的决定还为时过早。\NNo, Steve. It's too early for decisions like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.00,0:23:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我说我们要着陆。\NI said we are landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.13,0:23:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,理查德。 告诉我着陆点。\NRichard, show in the landing area.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.21,0:23:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你们将要在这里着陆，在峡谷里。\NYou'll land here, in the valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.80,0:23:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,在那里是着陆是天气条件最好的。\NThe weather conditions for descent are optimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.05,0:23:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,行了, 开始分离程序。\NWe're ready.Initiate un-docking procedure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.35,0:23:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"开始分离程序"。\N{\i1}Un-docking sequence initiated.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.85,0:24:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"引擎启动"\N{\i1}Engine's activated.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.77,0:24:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"高度30,000 米。 下降中"\N{\i1}The height is 30,000 meters. Coming down.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.46,0:25:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,一场风暴正在靠近。\NA storm front is heading your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.33,0:25:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,这风暴几分钟前才形成的，没法预测。\N{\i1}It formed a few minutes ago.Couldn't have predicted it.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.59,0:25:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,风速每秒 40 米\N{\i1}The winds are up to 40 meters per second.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.30,0:25:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,各位稳住咯。减速喷射器启动。\NSo hold on.Activating braking thrusters.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.43,0:25:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,卧槽怎么回事？\NWhat the hell was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.89,0:25:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,外面怎么了？                      风暴。\N{\i1}- What's going on?{\i}   -It's the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.52,0:25:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,雷暴好像相当猛烈。\NThe storm is quite aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.61,0:25:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我们以两倍的下降速度移动。 我们正在坠落！\NThe descent is twice as high as the landing speed. We're falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.94,0:25:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这样我们会坠毁在星球表面上！\NWe're gonna crush into surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.69,0:25:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以加倍喷射速度，可以降低你们的下降速度。\NI can double the thrust.It will slow your fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.74,0:25:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果我们这样做，我们就没有燃料飞回去了！\N{\i1}If we use that we won't have a fuel for the return flight!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.66,0:25:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,如果不这样做，我们也会死。\NIf we don't, we will die!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.46,0:25:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,温度太高了。你们的飞船外壳正在融化。\NThe temperature is too extreme. Your hole is melting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.33,0:25:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,操！ 把第一罐燃料用了吧！\NDamn it!Release the first tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.35,0:26:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我正在试着以改变姿态的方式减速。\NI'll try to slow you down aerodynamically.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.31,0:26:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,希望这飞船能撑得住。\NI hope the hole holds up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.57,0:26:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,抓稳了！接近地面!\N{\i1}Hold on.We are coming in on it!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.99,0:26:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,准备撞击！\N{\i1}Brace for impact!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.56,0:26:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,艾米？\NAmy…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.73,0:26:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,艾米……你这是要去哪？\NAmy, why did you fly off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.94,0:26:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要你。\NI need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.96,0:27:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我给你带了点东西。\NI got you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.83,0:27:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么？\NWhat's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.25,0:27:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在一起一年了。\NWe've been together for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.34,0:27:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，这"球体"对我来说意义重大。\NYou know, The Sphere means a lot to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.05,0:27:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,但远比不上你在我心中的地位。\Nbut not as much as you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.93,0:27:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,老实说，我知道你们两个不太处。\NObviously, I know you two don't get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.18,0:27:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么我想创造一些连接你们俩的东西。\NSo I thought to create something to connect you both.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.39,0:27:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这是原来"球体"的一部分。\NIt's made out of the old Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.90,0:27:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,它曾经是一块碎片,但也十分奇特。\NThere was a fragment that really stood out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.90,0:27:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,挺漂亮的。 谢谢你。\NIt's so beautiful. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.90,0:27:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得这是一种象征。\NI thought it would be symbolic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.74,0:27:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"球体"是人类的救赎的途径。\NThe Sphere is our salvation,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.70,0:27:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,而你也是我的救赎。\Nand you are mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.17,0:27:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我们回家吧。 草坪洒水器准备开始喷水了。\NLet's go home. The sprinklers are about to start spraying.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.59,0:27:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,再待一会吧。\NLet's stay for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.39,0:28:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,飞船状况如何？没有受到致命损伤\N-What's the status on the lander? No critical damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.11,0:28:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,但燃料快用完了。\NBut it's almost out of fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.40,0:29:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,现在没法回到船上，我们被困在这里。\NNow we can't get back to the ship,we're stuck here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.61,0:29:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么要回到船上？\NWhy go back to the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.99,0:29:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我们 4 年内才回去。\NOur plan was to come back in four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.33,0:29:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们的主要任务是设置和初始化"球体"。\NAnd now our main task is to install and launch the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.37,0:29:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我们继续这个计划。\NWe're continuing the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.12,0:29:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,但现在我们没法继续我们的计划。\NBut we can't carry it out now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.42,0:29:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在山谷里,离计划着陆区太远了。\NWe strayed too far away from the landing site, into the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.96,0:29:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着这里一定有洞穴。\NThat means there should be caves here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.72,0:29:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,然而，在这样的地形上是不可能放置穹顶的。\NBut it's impossible to deploy domes on this terrain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.22,0:29:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,没有穹顶也能完成我们的计划。\NWe'll manage without domes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.39,0:29:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,一个足够深的洞穴将为球体提供恰到好处的保护。\NA deep enough cave will provide the right amount of protection for the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.60,0:29:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,这里，这个洞穴看起来很合适。\NThere! This cave looks suitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.19,0:29:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,它够大而且很近。\NIt's big enough and easy to access.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.61,0:29:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Leona，获取地震活动数据。\NLeona, you get the data on seismic activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.86,0:29:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫，调整计划。\NDavid, adjust the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.53,0:29:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,其他人, 检查装备。\NEveryone else, check the equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.95,0:29:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,动身吧，伙计们。 还在等什么？\NGet to work, people,what are you waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.05,0:31:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这个星球上的条件比我们预期的还要好。\NConditions on this planet are even better than we expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.06,0:31:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,其他船只很快就会来到这里。\NOther ships will arrive here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.77,0:31:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,人类的新历史从这一刻开始。\NA new history of mankind begins here,at this very minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.14,0:33:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我们做到了，真是难以置信。\NWe did it! I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.15,0:33:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,如果彼得看到了这些, 他会很高兴的。他为此努力了太多。\NPeter would be so happy.He worked so hard for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.94,0:33:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,船长，你应该看看这个。\N{\i1}Captain, you need to see this.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.65,0:33:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他本应该在这里。\NHe should be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.86,0:33:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,好的，注意了船员们。\NOkay, attention, team.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.78,0:33:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在返回基地。\NWe're returning to base.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.45,0:33:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧。\NMove out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.92,0:34:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫,  我们有数据吗？\NDavid, do you have any data?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.01,0:34:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,还没有。\NNot yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.30,0:34:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,罗斯医生，军事法现在在这个驻地生效。\NDoctor Ross, martial lawsare in effect on this station.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.02,0:34:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,啥？ 为什么？\NWhat? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.27,0:34:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有新的消息。\NWe have new information.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.02,0:34:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,理查德？\NRichard?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.94,0:34:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,开始播放。\NStarting playback.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.37,0:34:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是 彼得雷曼 博士。\N{\i1}This is Dr. Peter Lehmann.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.79,0:34:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,很抱歉我违反命令，独自检查发动机。\N{\i1}Against all orders, I will personally conduct an Engine inspection.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.04,0:34:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我将记录我的所有操作\N{\i1}I'm now recording all of my actions{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.80,0:34:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,以免我受到无关的指责。\N{\i1}so I'm not accused of tampering with the results.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.59,0:34:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,安全摄像头已关闭所以没人可以干扰到我。\N{\i1}The security cameras are switched off so that I am not interrupted.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.47,0:34:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会成为替罪羊。\N{\i1}I'm not gonna be a scapegoat.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.56,0:35:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我会证明我没有犯错。\N{\i1}I'm gonna prove that I made no mistake.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.94,0:35:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,救命！\N{\i1}Help!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.66,0:36:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那是什么鬼东西？\NWhat was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.91,0:36:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,某种生命？\NSome kind of a life form?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.25,0:36:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,就是那玩意杀死彼得的吗？\NWas that what killed Peter?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.54,0:36:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我看了所有的监控记录。\N{\i1}I watched all of the recordings from the cameras.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.73,0:36:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,它就出现在球体旁边。\N{\i1}It shows up by the Sphere for the first time{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.89,0:36:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,自从我们离开地球后\N{\i1}right after we left Earth.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.34,0:36:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,那东西是不是从球体里跑出来了？\NThis thing crawled out of the Sphere?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.51,0:36:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,什么特洛伊木马故事。\NStraight outta the story of the Trojan horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.81,0:36:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,而那个特洛伊木马就在飞船跃迁之前爬进了引擎。\N{\i1}And that Trojan climbed right into the Engine just before the jump.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.19,0:36:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,那么我们跃迁失败就是那玩意造成的？\NSo maybe it caused the failure?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.44,0:36:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,理查德，那如果那个"特洛伊"还在船上，那你就有危险了。\NRichard, if that Trojan is still on the ship, you're in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.82,0:36:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,不, 它和你一起下去了。\NNo. He went down with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.87,0:36:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,进到了"球体"里面。\N{\i1}into the Sphere.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.95,0:36:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以追踪"它"的位置。\N{\i1}We can track its position.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.49,0:36:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,这东西对电磁场有干扰。\NIt causes interference in the electromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.25,0:36:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,这是相机在着陆前录制的视频。\N{\i1}Here's the video from the cameras right before the landing.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.59,0:36:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我从洞穴中得到了最初的数据。\NI've got the first data from the cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.13,0:36:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,有什么不正常的，史蒂夫?\NSomething's strange. Steve?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.98,0:37:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"球体"内的二氧化碳和氧化作用正在上升，\NLevels of CO2 and oxidation inside the Sphere are rising,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.36,0:37:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,但是没有生命的迹象。\Nbut there aren't any bio markers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.57,0:37:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,什么？会不会出故障了？\NWhat? Could it be a malfunction?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.99,0:37:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不，它正在满负荷运行。\NNo, it's working in a full capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.37,0:37:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,它运行了和我们预期不同的程序。\NJust on the different program than the one we've uploaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.41,0:37:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,它...它正在做其他事情。\NIt's doing something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.92,0:37:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,整队。\NRegroup.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.67,0:37:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要回到"球体"那。 我们需要改变设置。\NWe're going back to the Sphere.We need to adjust the settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.92,0:37:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫，没人会离开。\NNobody's going anywhere, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.63,0:37:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在消除了威胁之后，我们会进行处理程序的问题。\NWe'll adjust the settings later,after we deal with the threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.85,0:37:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,但史蒂夫是该项目的负责人，他发号施令。\NBut Steve is the head of the project,he calls the shots.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.52,0:37:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,不再是了。\NNot anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.23,0:37:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,从现在开始，一切都是为了船员的生存。\NNow it's a question of the crew survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.92,0:37:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫，现在我指挥，你被架空了。\NSteve, I'm taking command,you're being relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.65,0:37:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能这样！\NYou can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.40,0:37:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,这个任务决定着人类的未来！\NThe future of mankind depends on this mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.32,0:37:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,只有罗斯 博士 可以弄明白！\NOnly Dr. Ross can carry it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.53,0:38:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定罗斯博士老实告诉了我们\NAre you sure that Dr. Ross is giving us all the information
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.95,0:38:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,这个"球体"到底是什么了吗?\Nabout what the Sphere actually is?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.66,0:38:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你什么意思？\NWhat are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.75,0:38:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,理查德, 给我看洞穴的录像。\NRichard, show the video from the cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.93,0:38:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫看到了异常。\NSteve saw the anomaly.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.64,0:38:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,而且他没有告诉其他人。\NAnd didn't say anything to anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.31,0:38:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他全体船员的生命危险置于危险而不顾。\N{\i1}risking the lives of the entire crew.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.52,0:38:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,哪儿来的呢？                  来自那个"球体"。\N-Where did it come from?     -Right from the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.45,0:38:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,事实证明，我们对"球体"知之甚少。\NWhich as it turns out we know too little about.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.57,0:38:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,如果它是某种怪物的孵化器呢？\NWhat if it's an incubator for those monsters?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.99,0:38:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,对于"球体"的真相我对你没有任何隐瞒。\NI didn't hide a single confirmed fact about the Sphere from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.29,0:38:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,现在讨论这些异常没有意义。\NAnd there was no sense in discussing anomalies.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.09,0:38:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们知道这些异常\NIf we had known about these anomalies,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.34,0:38:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就不会以这样的方式处理"球体"。\Nwe would have treated the Sphere differently,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.93,0:39:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,而且彼得现在应该还活着。\Nand Peter would be alive right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.63,0:39:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫，很抱歉我没能成功。\NDavid, I'm sorry I couldn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.13,0:39:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,没关系。\NIt's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.26,0:39:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你很忙。\NI understand how busy you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.55,0:39:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,对, 我们也没有时间可以浪费。\NYes, we don't have much time to spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.02,0:39:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你在这干啥？\NWhy are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.48,0:39:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,医生说我没事。 他给了我健康报告。\NThe doctor says I'm fine.Gave me a clean bill of health.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.06,0:39:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我准备好加入预发射团队。\NSo I'm ready to join everyone for the pre-launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.57,0:39:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,什么？\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.74,0:39:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那么你...\NI mean you…
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.45,0:40:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你真的打算加入这个计划吗？\NYou're actually planning to fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.82,0:40:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,是你让我成为船员。\NBut you are the one who made me a member of the crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.70,0:40:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但那是之前的事了...\NBut that was before…
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.33,0:40:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,丽塔去世前？ 所以呢？\NBefore Rita died?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.92,0:40:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我告诉你，心理学家证实我很好。\NSo what?I'm telling you the psychologist has confirmed I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.97,0:40:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,但你的女儿...\NBut to lose a daughter…
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.47,0:40:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫，我很抱歉。\NDavid, I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.68,0:40:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你想回去工作，\NI understand you want to get back to work
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.39,0:40:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但这不是忘记悲伤的最好方法,\Nbut this is not the best way.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.73,0:40:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在需要时间缅怀。\NRight now you need time to grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.77,0:40:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫，我不是为了忘记我的女儿而飞。\NSteve, I'm not flying to forget my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.36,0:40:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我的女儿永远是我的一部分。\NShe'll always be a part of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.24,0:40:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我和你一样了解"球体"。\NI know the Sphere as well as you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.32,0:40:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在那里你会需要我。\NAnd you'll need me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.37,0:40:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫,听着。\NDavid, listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.54,0:40:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我所做的就是照顾你。\Nall I'm doing is looking out for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.12,0:40:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,什么？\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.62,0:40:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你把我除名了?\NYou're crossing my name off?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.00,0:40:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,在我们取得这一切之后，你就这样抛弃我？\NAfter all we've done you're going to leave me on the sidelines?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.59,0:41:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以帮你改变未来。\NI can help you change the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.60,0:41:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,不要带走我的这个机会。\NDon't take that away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.28,0:41:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,干啥？\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.49,0:41:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不能就这么走了。\NWe can't leave it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.20,0:41:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须回到洞穴并恢复我们的目标设置。\NWe have to go back to the cave and restore the settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.83,0:41:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但瑞恩有命令。\N-But Ryan gave orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.34,0:41:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,就我俩。\N-Just you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.88,0:41:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我们悄悄地去。\NWe'll go out quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.46,0:41:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,杀死了彼得的那玩意还在那儿。\NWhatever killed Peter is still in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.63,0:41:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,"特洛伊"目前距离洞穴 30 公里远。\NThe Trojan is 30 kilometers away from the cave right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.97,0:41:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着如果那"东西"要回来......\Nthat means if it decides to come back
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.91,0:41:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我们至少还有半个小时撤离。\Nwe'll have at least half an hour to get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.45,0:41:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 瑞恩呢？\N-What about Ryan?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.31,0:41:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- 瑞恩谨慎过度了。\N-Ryan's too careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.31,0:41:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他在浪费时间！\NHe's wasting time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.02,0:42:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,时间就是生命。\NLost days are lost lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.32,0:42:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,丽塔去世后，你的一部分也随着丽塔逝去。\NWhen Rita was dying,you slowly died with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.70,0:42:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道那是怎么样的感觉。\NI saw what that was like.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.16,0:42:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,现在想象我们的家园以同样的方式死亡。\NNow imagine that entire planet is dying the exact same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.96,0:42:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,慢慢地，不可逆转的毁灭，因为同一种病毒。\NSlowly, irreversibly,from the same virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.98,0:42:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我草这是什么？\NWhat the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.90,0:42:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了？\NWhat's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.82,0:42:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,这些都是"球体"干的。\NThe Sphere did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.36,0:42:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你认为这是故障吗？\N-You think it was a malfunction?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.09,0:42:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,这不止是故障。\N-Not just a malfunction
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.66,0:42:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"球体"创造了一种外星生命形式。\NThe Sphere is creating an alien life form.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.78,0:42:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,而且相当快。\NAnd incredibly quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.91,0:42:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,比它在地球上创造生命的速度还要快。\NFaster than it created life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.41,0:42:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不该碰它，应该和所有人都讨论一下。\NWe shouldn't touch it.We need to discuss this with everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.21,0:43:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要制定一个行动计划。\NWe need to set a plan of action.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.42,0:43:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,有人调整了"球体"的设置。\NSomeone readjusted the settings on the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.80,0:43:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"特洛伊"正在逼近。 我们该走了！\NThe Trojan's getting closer,we gotta leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.18,0:43:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,在等一会。\NJust a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.47,0:43:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你没听见吗？\NCan't you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.43,0:43:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,这犯不着你拿命去赌。 快走！\NThere's no point in risking our lives!Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.06,0:43:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,离我远点！ 该死的！\NGet away from me, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.28,0:43:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你疯了吗？\NHave you lost your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.77,0:43:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,完了！ 任务失败！\NIt's over! The mission is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.78,0:43:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,承认吧！\NDeal with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.74,0:43:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"球体"有敌意！\NThe Sphere is hostile!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.58,0:43:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,放下枪，大卫！ 快放下！\NPut the gun down, David! Put it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.04,0:43:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你想为这个垃圾玩意去死？\NYou wanna die because of this piece of shit?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.46,0:43:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,太迟了, 它已经在发展了。\NToo late, it's already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.18,0:45:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"气闸关闭"\N{\i1}Airlock closed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.19,0:45:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"加压完成"\N{\i1}Pressurization completed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.56,0:45:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈真是疯了，史蒂夫。 因为你，我们差点死了。\NYou're a psycho, Steve.Because of you, we both almost died.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.28,0:45:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,这不关我们的事。我们必须得完成任务。\NThis is not about us.We have to complete the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.45,0:45:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你损坏了"球体"，我们一切努力都将付诸东流。\NIf you had damaged the Sphere all of this would've been for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.25,0:45:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,那你就该开枪打死我！那你为什么不呢？\NThen you should've shot me.Why didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.17,0:46:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你再次危及任务...\NIf you threaten the mission one more time
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.47,0:46:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我会的。\NI will.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.60,0:46:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫，你在做什么？你去哪儿了？\NSteve, what the hell were you doing?Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.19,0:46:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么违背我的命令离开着陆器？\NWhy did you leave the lander against my orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.69,0:46:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我们做了我们必须做的。\NWe did what we had to.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.79,0:46:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你没有权利指挥我们。\NYou no longer have the right to make decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.62,0:46:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我做了我认为该做的事。\NI make the decisions I find necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.58,0:46:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,不然呢？\NOr what?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.63,0:46:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你你会怎么做？暴力？\NWhat are you gonna do?Use force?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.88,0:46:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,那来啊!\NThen go ahead! Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.09,0:46:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,来打啊!\NCome on!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.73,0:46:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"模块完整性错误"\N{\i1}Module integrity compromised.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.15,0:46:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你做了什么？\NWhat did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.44,0:46:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"模块完整性错误"\N{\i1}Module integrity compromised.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.19,0:47:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,"模块完整性错误"\N{\i1}Module integrity compromised.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.41,0:48:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,安静点，亲爱的。\NQuiet, sweetie.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.29,0:48:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们差点失去理智。\NWe're so close I'm losing my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.62,0:48:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,那是什么？\NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.34,0:48:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"特洛伊"已经进来了。\NTrojan's in the lander.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.84,0:48:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他接管了我们的系统，我们有大麻烦了。\NGot a hole in the lower deck,everything's covered in this shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.55,0:48:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，我们现在该怎么办？\NSo what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.10,0:48:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,静谧行动,走吧\NQuietly, and slowly. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.70,0:49:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,喘不上气啊。\NIt's hard to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.68,0:49:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,回去吧。\NGet back.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.81,0:49:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,哈？ 为什么？\NWhat? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.81,0:49:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"他"在这儿。\NIt's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.59,0:50:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,快跑。\NRun!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.36,0:50:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么回事？ 你俩还好吗？\NWhat's happened?Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.90,0:50:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"特洛伊"!\NThe Trojan…
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.28,0:50:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,"特洛伊"在实验室！\NThe Trojan's in the laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.70,0:50:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道你俩做了什么蠢事吗？\NDo you realize what you've done?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.41,0:50:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你把那玩意带下来了！\NYou brought it down here with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.56,0:51:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,它能进来吗？\N-Can it get in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.60,0:51:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我们没法知道。\N-We don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.85,0:51:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,它损坏了发电机，摄像机无法工作。\NIt damaged the generator and the cameras aren't working.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.02,0:51:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我们与母舰失去了联系。\NWe've lost contact with the ship, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.36,0:51:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我们无法得到太空传来的录像！\NWe have no video from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.65,0:51:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这是系统中录制的最后一个视频。\NHere's the last video saved on the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.82,0:51:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这东西正在寻找船体的薄弱处。\NIt was looking for a weak spot in the hull.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.16,0:51:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,它进入了冷却系统。\NIt got in through the cooling system.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.96,0:51:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,那里的钢板最薄。\NWhere the steel is thinnest.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.37,0:51:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,所以这个东西有智慧?它会思考?\NSo this thing is smart?It can think?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.34,0:51:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不管它有没有脑子……\NWhether it can think or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.59,0:51:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们把它熏出去把洞给补上，它就不能再爬进来了。\Nif we smoke it out and with the hole shut it can't crawl back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.05,0:51:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但该怎么做？ 我们如何把它弄出来？\NBut how? How can we smoke it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.05,0:51:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我们甚至不知道它在哪。\NWe can't even see where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.14,0:51:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要重启安全摄像头和通讯。\NWe have to restore the security cameras and communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.02,0:51:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,"特洛伊"损坏了主发电机。但是维生系统仍然在工作。\NThe Trojan damaged the main generator,but the life support system is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.90,0:51:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着备用发电机没有坏。\NThat means the back up generator is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.61,0:51:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以将网络和摄像头连接到备用电机。\NWe can connect the network and cameras to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.49,0:51:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我们一路摸黑保险丝盒那！\NWe will have to make all the way blind to the fuse box
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.96,0:52:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,而且不知道这狗杂种在哪里\Nwith no idea where that bastard is.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.94,0:52:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,这太冒险了。\NIt's too risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.54,0:52:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,都是我的错。\NIt's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.00,0:52:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,那我去。\NSo I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.09,0:52:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我会掩护你背后。\NI'll watch your six.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.01,0:54:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫！\NSteve,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.01,0:54:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,快离开那里, 现在！\N{\i1}you need to get out of there, now!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.94,0:55:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,受伤了吗？\NAre you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.61,0:55:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,信号和摄像头怎么样？\NHow's the signal and the cameras?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.78,0:55:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,一切正常，重新上线。\NAll there. Back online.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.74,0:55:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,该死，它发射的电磁场比球体还要强！\NDamn it! It's transmitting an EMP field stronger than the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.95,0:55:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,它旁边的那些电子设备要坏了。\NThe electronics next to it are going crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.58,0:55:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,现在怎么办？\NSo what now?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.67,0:55:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你曾经见过一头愤怒的公牛追逐那些奔跑的人们吗？\NHave you ever seen a raging bull running after the crowds
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.57,0:55:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,在人牛正式对决之前, 有一条狭窄的巷子\Ndown a narrow passage just before a bull fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.68,0:55:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,愤怒的公牛想要逮住那些逃跑的人\NThe bull wants to catch the runners,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.14,0:56:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但巷子最终会将公牛和斗牛士在带到竞技场上对决。\Nbut he ends up in the arena with the matador.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.56,0:56:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,现在"特洛伊"就是那头公牛。他也想抓住我们。\NThe Trojan is the bull.It also wants to catch us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.52,0:56:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有机会将它带到任何我们想要的地方，例如在着陆器外。\NWe have a chance to lead it wherever we want, like outside the lander.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.32,0:56:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都承受着巨大的风险。\NIt's a huge risk for everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.11,0:56:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,但这将是值得的。\Nbut it's all worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.63,0:56:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,着陆器有 2 个气闸。\NThe lander has two airlocks:
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.68,0:56:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,在一个在中心另一个在实验室。\Nthe central one, and the one in the lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.26,0:56:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我会在在中央舱门前的外边。\NI'll be outside in front of the open central hatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.31,0:56:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我做主要诱饵。\NI'll be the main decoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.23,0:56:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"特洛伊"会追着我穿过走廊。\NThe Trojan will chase me along the corridors.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.77,0:56:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦我们到了外面，你要关闭它身后的引擎气闸。\NOnce we get outside, you'll shut the engines to the airlock behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.74,0:56:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,明白了吗？\NUnderstood?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.09,0:56:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但要做到这一切，我们必须去气闸。\NBut in order to do all that,we need to get to the airlocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.79,0:56:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是"特洛伊"所在的地方。\NAnd that's where the Trojan is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.29,0:56:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以把它孤立在主走廊里, 这.\NWe can isolate it in the main corridor, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.54,0:57:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,内部舱门没法关住它太久。\NThe inner doors won't hold on long,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.67,0:57:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,但应该为能我们争取一些时间。\Nbut should buy us some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.86,0:57:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我会将它引入内盖所在的区域并把他锁在那里。\N{\i1}I'll lure him into the inter-hatch space.And lock him in{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.92,0:58:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,在"特洛伊"被关起来后，我们每个人都要到特定的地点。\N{\i1}After the Trojan is blocked, each one of us will report to a specific location.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.96,0:58:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫，你和我将打开实验室的气闸。\N{\i1}David, you and I will open the air hatch in the labs.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.18,0:58:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,当我出去引诱"特洛伊"时，你在那里等我。\N{\i1}You'll wait for me there,while I'll go outside to be the bait for the Trojan.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.81,0:58:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,但是为了确保"特洛伊"看到我并出来...\NBut in order for the Trojan to see me and come out
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.35,0:58:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,两侧的气闸都必须打开。\Nboth sides of the airlock have to be open,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.23,0:58:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,外面和里面的。\Noutside and inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.94,0:58:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 Leona 得手动打开气闸。\NThat's why Leona will manually open the airlock
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.20,0:58:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,然后就躲在科技仓那。\Nand hide right here,in the technical bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.60,0:59:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,当特洛伊追上我时，它会跑到这里。\N{\i1}When the Trojan comes after me,it will run over here,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.40,0:59:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,穿过发动机喷嘴。\N{\i1}past the Engine's steering nozzles.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.02,0:59:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,应该还剩有一些燃料。\N{\i1}There should be some fuel left.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.98,0:59:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们在正确的时刻启动引擎...\N{\i1}And if we turn the Engine at the right moment{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.95,0:59:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,...我们不只是把它轰出去，我们烤熟他。\N{\i1}we won't just smoke it out,we'll roast it.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.91,0:59:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,滚开，这该死的混蛋！\N{\i1}Get out of here, you fucking bastard!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.54,0:59:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,动作快！ 这门要坚持不住了。\N{\i1}Hurry! It won't hold up much longer!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.04,0:59:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,别慌。 把"特洛伊"引导出来。\NDon't panic. Release the Trojan.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.42,0:59:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,好好躲在技术舱。\NHide in the tech bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.58,0:59:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你做得到。\NYou can do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.36,1:00:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我正在启动引擎。\N{\i1}I'm turning on the Engine.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.61,1:00:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,引擎没有启动，"特洛伊"正扰乱乱系统！\NIt's not working.The Trojan is messing with the system.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.16,1:00:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫，快跑！\NSteve, run!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.83,1:00:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,引擎启动了。\NThe Engine's on.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.25,1:00:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,蕾欧娜，出去！ 快出去！\NLeona, get out! Get out!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.81,1:01:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞恩，气闸！ 快关闭气闸！\N{\i1}Ryan, the airlock!Shut the airlock!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.11,1:01:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,草。\NShit!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.55,1:01:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,安息吧，弗兰克。\NRest in peace, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.87,1:02:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,舱门切断了它的一部分触手。它回山洞去了。\NA part of its tentacle was cut off by the door. It returned to the cave.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.30,1:02:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"加压完成"\N{\i1}Pressurization complete.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.80,1:02:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"氧气水平正在恢复正常"\N{\i1}Oxygen level returning to normal.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.85,1:02:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,它回不来了。\NIt won't get back in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.19,1:02:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,但那玩意控制"球体"了。\NBut the Sphere is under its control.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.61,1:02:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,不会持续太久的。\NNot for long.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.07,1:02:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,艾米？\NAmy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.70,1:02:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么？\NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.21,1:02:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,病毒。\NIt's the virus…
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.33,1:02:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,老实说.病毒已经在我们的家园之中了。\NIt's already in our home, literally.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.63,1:02:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你不应该去执行这个任务。\NYou shouldn't go on this mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.55,1:02:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,艾米，你在胡说什么呢？我想我们已经都谈妥了。\NAmy, what are you talking about?We discussed everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.60,1:02:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你已经做得够多的了，这不是你的任务。\NYou've done enough.This isn't your mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.10,1:03:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 拜托.         - 你甚至都不是宇航员。\N-Excuse me? -You're not even an astronaut.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.03,1:03:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你想让我在发射前一周离开？\NYou want me to walk out a week before the launch?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.82,1:03:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么回事？\NWhat's gotten into you?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.04,1:03:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要有孩子了。\NWe're going to have a baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.38,1:03:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,什么？\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.34,1:03:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,留下来吧,\NJust stay.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.22,1:03:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,疫苗也是我们的希望。我找到了一个有前途的方法！\NWe'll work on the vaccine.I found a promising pathway.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.93,1:03:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,这任务将创造一个新地球，但我们也可以拯救我们的地球。\NThe mission will create a new Earth but we could save this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.27,1:03:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我疫苗的蓝图, 看看吧。\NThis is my blueprint for the vaccine,please go over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.46,1:03:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,这让我真的很开心。\NI'm really happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.06,1:03:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但是时间紧迫。\NBut it's such poor timing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.82,1:03:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我也许没法看到我们的孩子成长了。\NI won't get to see him grow up.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.86,1:03:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫！ 我恳求你, 留在我身边，留在我们的身边！\NSteve, I'm begging you.Please, stay with me. Stay with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.91,1:03:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,对不起，我得去做我们的任务。我必须去的。\NI can't, I have to be there. I have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.41,1:04:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你已经尽你所能了。\NYou've done everything you could.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.37,1:04:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以开发疫苗，我认为这是有用的！\NWe can develop the vaccine now.I think I'm onto something.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.88,1:04:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我得拯救地球。\NI need to save the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.18,1:04:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要研究这种生物，\NWe have to study this creature,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.03,1:04:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这样我们才能了解你感染了什么。\Nso we can understand what you're infected with.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.03,1:04:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜它是一种生物机器。\NMy guess, it's a bio-robot.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.55,1:05:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他们与"球体"的材料相同。\NThese are the same materials the Sphere is made of.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.69,1:05:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,当它们接触到水时，就会改变它们的特性。\NAnd they also change their properties when they come into contact with water.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.07,1:05:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我们研究了它，但从未了解\NWe studied it never understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.82,1:05:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,它的功能之一是创造"特洛伊"\Nthat one of its functions was to create a Trojan.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.08,1:05:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,也许它比我们先进得多。\NMaybe they are much more advanced than we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.71,1:05:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,而且更好。\NAnd better.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.77,1:05:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫,听着。\NDavid, listen…
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.48,1:05:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我你发现了什么。\NTell me what you found.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.48,1:06:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,感染你的细菌...\NThe bacteria that infected you
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.61,1:06:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,...具有异常强大的防御机制。\Nhave an unusually powerful defense mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.58,1:06:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,经过我的调查，\NI studied them.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.34,1:06:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我弄清楚了它的原理。\NFigured out how they work.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.30,1:06:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我们千辛万苦所寻找的。\NThis is what we spent all those years searching for.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.05,1:06:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你的血液就是制备对抗...\NYour blood holds the key to the vaccine against the virus
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.91,1:06:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,摧毁我们家园病毒疫苗的关键\Nthat's been destroying life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.65,1:06:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,这不会改变任何事情。\NIt doesn't change anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.31,1:06:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你还不明白吗？\NDon't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.65,1:06:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以拯救世界。\NWe can save the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.24,1:06:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,而这一切是因为你。你是真正的英雄。\NAnd it's all because of you.You are the real hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.16,1:06:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我会给你止痛药。你会感觉好点的。\NI'll administer some painkillers,you'll feel better.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.76,1:07:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,那就来吧。\NHere goes nothing…
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.25,1:08:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,那是什么？\NWhat was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.13,1:08:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫...\NDavid…
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.00,1:08:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个应答器。\NIt's a transponder.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.88,1:08:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以看到这些与"球体"的联系。\NWe can see the connections of the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.85,1:08:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,这是他们殖民行星的方式。\NThis is their way of colonizing planets.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.77,1:08:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么回事？\N{\i1}How's it going?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.19,1:08:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个生物机器人。\N{\i1}It's a bio-robot.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.02,1:08:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须想办法摧毁它\N{\i1}We have to find a way to destroy it{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.40,1:08:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,并且重置"球体"。\Nand restore the settings in the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.23,1:08:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,不，史蒂夫。 已经有太多人因为你而死了。\N{\i1}No, Steve. Too many people have died because of you already.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.66,1:08:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,等会,你做了什么？\N{\i1}Wait. What did you do?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.37,1:09:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你把我锁在里面了吗？\N{\i1}Did you lock me in?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.91,1:09:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你被捕了，史蒂夫。\N{\i1}You are under arrest, Steve.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.33,1:09:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞安...\N{\i1}Ryan,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.17,1:09:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须共同努力.\N{\i1}we have to work together.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.84,1:09:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,为了彼得、弗兰克和莱昂娜。\N{\i1}For Peter, and Frank and Leona.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.88,1:09:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,否则，他们会白白死去。\N{\i1}Otherwise they all died in vain--{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.68,1:09:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,对你来说,同伴只不过是消耗品。\N{\i1}People are expendable to you.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.72,1:09:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞恩！ 瑞恩！ 瑞恩！\N{\i1}Ryan! Ryan!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.77,1:09:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他是对的。\NHe's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.24,1:09:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,人类的救赎对你来说从来都不是重要的，史蒂夫。\NIt was never the salvation of humanity that was most important to you, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.49,1:09:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你一直想扮演英雄。\NYou always wanna play the hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.66,1:09:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,而现在你想要的就是赢。你也不关心其他人的死活。\NAnd now you just want to win and you don't care about other people's lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.02,1:10:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,艾米，回答我。\NAmy, talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.78,1:10:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经看过了你的提案。 它看起来真的很有希望。\NI read your proposal.It looks truly promising.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.83,1:10:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,一个真正的突破\NA real breakthrough.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.08,1:10:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,一个研制疫苗的机会,确实很有希望。\NA chance to create a vaccine.Finally, a real one.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.01,1:10:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,但我还是得去。为了我们好。\NBut I do need to go.For our sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.18,1:10:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,没有你我不知道该怎么办。\NI don't know what I'll do without you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.06,1:10:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我保证, 我会回来的。\Nbut I promise I'll come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.40,1:11:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要你。\NI need you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.73,1:11:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你和我们的孩子。\NBoth of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.16,1:11:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我们的儿子...\NTell him…
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.95,1:11:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,...或者我们的女儿...\Nor her…
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.46,1:11:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,...他的父亲将像上帝一样创造一个新地球。\Nthat Daddy like a God is out creating the new Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.92,1:11:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你总是这样说你为了拯救所有人才做的这些。\NYou keep saying you're doing this to save everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.47,1:11:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但是每个人又是谁？\NBut who is everyone?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.72,1:11:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在目中无人。\NYou don't see people around you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.64,1:11:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你只关心你自己, 和你的项目。有什么区别吗。\NAll you care about is you and your project. Why even bother?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.73,1:11:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你想被称赞为救世主吗？ 就这？\NTo be the hailed a savior? Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.24,1:11:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我想拯救我们的未来。\NTo save our future.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.95,1:11:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道你真正想要拯救的是什么。\NI wonder what it is you're really trying to save.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.90,1:12:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,理查德，你模拟了过最近恒星的轨道吗？\NRichard, you modeled the trajectories of the nearest stars?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.90,1:12:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,那样做什么都得不到。你觉得那有可能找到些什么吗？\NThat didn't give us anything.What do you think you'll find there?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.41,1:12:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在跃迁时你说过:\NYou said that when we made the jump
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.32,1:12:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你说我们沿着空间坐标轴穿越,然而这对我们来说是做不到的\Nwe moved along a coordinate axis that was inaccessible to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.62,1:12:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,如果这个轴不属于空间呢？\NAnd what if that axis wasn't spatial?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.38,1:12:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们看看这些星星应该的样子\NShow us how these stars will look
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.63,1:12:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,加入宇宙膨胀超过四十亿年的参数...\Naccounting the expansion of the universe over four billion years.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.97,1:12:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,行, 重新计算中。\N{\i1}Yes, recalculating.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.45,1:13:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我们并没有穿越空间。\NWe didn't move in space.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.62,1:13:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,而是穿越了时间。\NWe moved in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.41,1:13:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,这是大熊座(北斗七星)。\NIt's Ursa Major.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.70,1:13:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,和猎户座。\NAnd Orion.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.17,1:13:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,它就是 北极星。\NAnd there's the North Star…
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.54,1:13:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,而我们的...\Nand our…
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.30,1:13:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,太阳？\NSun?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.27,1:13:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,地球是一片死寂，\NAnd the Earth was silent and empty,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.10,1:13:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的深渊里一片黑暗。\Nand the darkness over the abyss.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.03,1:13:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,那意味着我们在地球上？\NThat means that we're on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.57,1:13:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,在生命开始之前？\NBefore the beginning of life itself?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.17,1:14:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,四十亿年前？\NAbout four billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.80,1:14:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你刚刚是怎么发现的？\NHow did you figure that out?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.52,1:14:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这是那块大卫开火时击落的碎片。\NThis is the fragment that flew off the Sphere when David fired at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.02,1:14:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,从"球体"击飞出的。那块碎片.\NHere is the broken fragment.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.40,1:14:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,和我为艾米做的手镯碎片一模一样。\NAnd here is the same pieceon the bracelet I made for Amy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.41,1:14:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这就是同一片碎片。\NBecause it's the exact same fragment.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.96,1:14:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我们这里的"球体"和地球上的旧"球体"……\NThe Sphere here and the old one on Earth
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.09,1:14:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...就是同一个"球体"。\Nare the exact same Sphere,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.05,1:14:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但是在不同的时间的同一个球体。\Nbut in different times.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.97,1:14:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,一些"文明"将"球体"送到地球。\NSome civilization sent the Sphere on Earth
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.26,1:15:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,为他们创造适合他们的生物圈。\Nto create a biosphere suitable for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.18,1:15:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但是出了点问题。\NBut something went wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.64,1:15:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但这意味着无论我们在这里做什么\NBut that means no matter what we do here,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.61,1:15:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都无法拯救地球上的人。\Nwe won't save the people on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.48,1:15:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,只剩下一个选项了。\NThere's only one option left,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.90,1:15:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉艾米这些外星细菌...\Ntell Amy about those extraterrestrial bacteria
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.03,1:15:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...将帮助她研制疫苗。\Nand help her to create the vaccine.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.58,1:15:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你打算怎么做？\NHow do you plan to do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.54,1:15:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们已经知道，这个球体仍会留在洞穴中直到我们重新发现它。\NWe know that the Sphere will remain in the cave until our time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.46,1:15:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,未来的我将会用这块碎片为艾米做手镯。\NAnd that I will make this fragment into a bracelet for Amy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.85,1:15:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我会给他写一条信息，告诉她如何连接"球体"。\NI'll write her a message telling her how to connect the Spheres.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.86,1:15:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,但在我们离开之前，艾米拿着手镯。\NBut Amy had the bracelet before we left.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.45,1:15:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,她什么也没说。\NAnd she didn't say anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.20,1:16:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信艾米会想念我的。\NI believe Amy will miss me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.83,1:16:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,她会来拿手镯，\NShe will come for the bracelet,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.96,1:16:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,早晚她都会看到这些铭文。\Nand sooner or later she will see these inscriptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.67,1:16:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,剩下的就是放回零件\NWhat's left is to put the part back
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.59,1:16:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,并重新调整系统。\Nand reconfigure the system.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.26,1:16:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,否则，我们所知道的生命与人性...\NOr the life that we ​​know
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.84,1:16:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,将永远不会出现。\Nwill never appear.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.05,1:16:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,人类也不会。\NNeither will humanity.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.56,1:18:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫! 史蒂夫！\N{\i1}Steve! Steve!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.90,1:18:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞恩计划炸毁"球体"。\NRyan is planning on blowing up the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.36,1:18:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,让我联系他\NConnect me to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.61,1:18:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,他把他的通讯关了。\NHe switched off his radio.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.82,1:18:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你得亲自找到他\NYou need to find him
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.91,1:18:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,并解释一切。\N{\i1}and explain everything.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.33,1:18:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,快走，我重新打开了气闸。\N{\i1}Go, I've re-opened the airlock.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.41,1:18:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,站住。\NStop right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.62,1:18:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞安\NRyan…
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.75,1:19:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,这"球体"是我们唯一的机会。\NThe Sphere is our only chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.13,1:19:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,想都别想\NDon't even try.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.38,1:19:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧, 行。\NOkay. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.72,1:19:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但你的计划仍然行不通。\NBut your plan still won't work.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.77,1:19:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,它可以。\NIt will.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.02,1:19:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你会知道的。\NYou'll see.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.56,1:19:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你想把炸弹带进洞穴。\NYou want to take the bomb to the cave,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.86,1:19:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你会等到"特洛伊"找到你。然后在那里炸毁"球体"和"特洛伊"。\Nwait for the Trojan there and blow it up along with the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.74,1:19:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,但是如果它在半路上攻击你怎么办？\NBut what if it attacks you on the way?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.66,1:19:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,那我也会继续计划\NThen I will go up
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.71,1:19:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,一起炸得渣都不剩\Nin smoke with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.50,1:19:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,然后你的计划失败。\NAnd you will lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.63,1:19:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,然后，"球体"将继续为"特洛伊"创造它所需要的环境。\NAfter all, the Sphere will continue to create the environment that the Trojan needs.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.97,1:19:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,那你有什么想法？你有更好的主意吗？\NWhat do you suggest?You got a better idea?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.77,1:19:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我们把"特洛伊"\NLet's lure in the Trojan,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.06,1:19:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,引进着陆器里。\Ninto the lander,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.15,1:20:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,关闭气闸然后把它炸上天。\Nlock the airlocks and blow it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.40,1:20:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,给你。\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.86,1:20:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫, 你干啥？\NDavid, why?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.95,1:20:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,为了丽塔！\NFor Rita.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.96,1:20:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,她死了！\NShe died.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.58,1:20:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,她还没死！\NShe hasn't died yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.29,1:20:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你疯了。\NYou're deranged.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.51,1:20:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我没疯。\NI'm not.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.63,1:20:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,在山洞里发生的那些事之后，我明白了。\NAfter what have happened in the cave, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.52,1:20:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"特洛伊"没有杀我。\NThe Trojan didn't kill me,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.22,1:20:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,而且它不会没有缘由地做事。\Nand it doesn't do anything without a reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.41,1:20:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,它选择了我！\NIt chose me.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.87,1:20:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我也会帮助它。\NAnd I will help it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.87,1:20:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不应该在这里。\NWe weren't supposed to be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.25,1:21:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在这出现是一个错误。\NWe're a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.54,1:21:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你是帮助我理解这一点的人。\NAnd you are the one who helped me understand that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.97,1:21:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道我们都一样，史蒂夫！\NI realized that we all are just like you, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.52,1:21:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不是天生的。\NWe weren't created right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.39,1:21:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是因为"球体"的故障...\NWe're a malfunction of the Sphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.11,1:21:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,但我会修复它。\NBut I will fix it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.03,1:21:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,大卫！ 别傻了！\NDavid, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.45,1:21:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能那样帮助丽塔！\NYou can't help Rita like that!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.66,1:21:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,她不是生来就受苦的。\NShe wouldn't be born to suffer,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.66,1:21:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,而且她8岁也不该死！\Nand she will not die at the age of eight.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.17,1:21:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,没有其他人会受苦，史蒂夫。\NNo ones else will suffer, Steve,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.97,1:21:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,因为人类不曾存在过！\Nbecause there will never be any people to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.31,1:22:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,人类应该有机会。 大卫。\NPeople deserve a chance, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.35,1:22:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,人类不曾改变过。\NPeople don't change.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.95,1:26:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,指挥部\N{\i1}Encounter to Mission.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.37,1:26:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,指挥部\NEncounter to Mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.08,1:26:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是指挥部\NEncounter to Mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.30,1:26:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,快接通啊\NCome in, Mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.47,1:26:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,加油，兄弟们\NCome on, guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.22,1:26:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是指挥部\NEncounter to Mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.85,1:27:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是指挥部\N{\i1}Encounter to Mission.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.81,1:27:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是指挥部\N{\i1}Encounter to Mission!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.36,1:27:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是指挥部\N{\i1}Encounter to Mission!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.53,1:27:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是指挥部\N{\i1}Encounter to Mission!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.70,1:27:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,理查德\NRichard
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.29,1:27:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫!感谢上帝！\NSteve! Thank God!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.87,1:27:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我在摄像机上看到了爆炸。\NI saw the explosion on camera.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.87,1:27:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为你们都在爆炸中丧生了...\N{\i1}I thought you were all…{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.97,1:27:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- 特洛伊被摧毁了。\N- The Trojan's been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.75,1:27:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞恩呢？\NWhat about Ryan?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.75,1:27:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他死了。\N{\i1}He didn't make it.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.06,1:27:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫。你的氧气水平下降。\N{\i1}Steve, your oxygen levels are dropping.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.85,1:27:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,看起来像我的氧气罐被碎片扎破了。\NLooks like some shrapnel pierced the tank.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.19,1:27:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我还有多少时间？\NHow much time do I have?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.97,1:27:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,大约一小时。\N{\i1}-About an hour.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.11,1:27:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,坚持，稍等。 我会开船下来接你。\N{\i1}Look, I'll land the ship and pick you up.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.41,1:28:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,不。这里有风暴, 你会坠毁的。\NNo, there's a storm here. You'll crash.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.74,1:28:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你接下来打算怎么办？\NAnd what are you gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.91,1:28:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我要返回洞穴,  我必须联系艾米。\N{\i1}I'm going to the cave.I need to contact Amy.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.17,1:28:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,风暴平息后，我会尽快降落。\NLand the ship as soon as the storm settles down.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.63,1:28:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,祝你好运，史蒂夫。\NGodspeed, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.23,1:30:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托,拜托别坏了\NPlease start working.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.09,1:30:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫！\NSteve!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.97,1:31:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,艾米？\NAmy?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.44,1:31:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫！\NSteve!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.53,1:31:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你在哪里？\NWhere are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.61,1:31:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我在某个地方, 在遥远的过去。\NI'm somewhere in the distant past.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.93,1:31:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你什么意思？\NWhat do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.66,1:31:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们没有太多时间。我想我知道该如何拯救地球。\NWe don't have much time.I know how to save the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.04,1:31:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你是对的。\NYou were on the right path.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.16,1:31:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,有一种机制, 可以帮助我们制造疫苗。\NThere's a mechanism that can help us create the vaccine.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.33,1:31:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我在这里亲眼看到了它。\NI saw it here with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.92,1:31:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在能记下来吗?\N-Can you write something down?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.83,1:31:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，当然。\NSure. Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.39,1:31:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你得帮助植物细胞\NYou have to teach the plant cells
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.10,1:31:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,教它快速识别病毒的任何变种。\Nto quickly identify any mutation of the virus.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.23,1:31:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,这是抗原配方。\NHere's the antigen formula.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.52,1:31:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,艾米，我曾答应过我会回来的。\NAmy, I promised I'd come back to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.77,1:32:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我想现在应该做不到了。\NI'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.57,1:32:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,不，史蒂夫。\NNo. Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.81,1:32:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我只后悔一件事。\NI only regret one thing…
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.29,1:32:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,就是我再也不能碰你了...\NThat I'll never hold you again
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.83,1:32:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,还有我们的孩子。\Nand our child.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.34,1:32:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我们仍然相互联系着，记得吗？\NWe're connected, remember?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.97,1:32:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你永远与我同在, 和我们同在。\NYou'll always be with me. With us.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.82,1:32:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱你, 爱你们俩。\NI love you. Both of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.00,1:32:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.54,1:33:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱你\NI love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.42,1:33:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂夫\NSteve
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.36,1:34:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,地球，受到了造物主的恩惠。\N{\i1}The Earth, O Lord,is full of God mercy.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.70,1:34:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你教给我规则\N{\i1}Teach me thy statutes.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.58,1:34:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,,告诉我给我常识和知识。\N{\i1}Teach me good judgment and knowledge.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.25,1:34:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我走向歧路, 受到了报应……\N{\i1}Before I was afflicted I went astray.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.34,1:34:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,但现在我信守你的格言。\N{\i1}But now have I kept thy word.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.51,1:34:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你创造了我，塑造了我。\N{\i1}Thy hands have made me and fashioned me.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.39,1:34:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,愿你的怜悯降临于我\N{\i1}Let thy tender mercies come unto me,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.48,1:34:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我以此得以生存。\N{\i1}that I may live.{\i}

